anemic.Name: anemic
anemic.Description: suffering from anemia. Anemia is a quantitative deficiency of the hemoglobin, often accompanied by a reduced number of red blood cells and causing pallor, weakness, and breathlessness.

boomer.Name: boomer
boomer.Description: a person born during a baby boom, especially one born in the U.S. between 1946 and 1965.

child.Name: child
child.Description: a person between birth and puberty or full growth.

deaf.Name: deaf
deaf.Description: partially or wholly lacking or deprived of the sense of hearing; unable to hear.

dehydrated.Name: dehydrated
dehydrated.Description: to be deprived (a chemical compound) of water or the elements of water.

fat.Name: fat
fat.Description: having too much flabby tissue; corpulent; obese.

hungry.Name: hungry
hungry.Description: having a desire, craving, or need for food; feeling hunger.

neurotic.Name: neurotic
neurotic.Description: of, relating to, or characteristic of neurosis.

novice.Name: novice
novice.Description: a person who is new to the circumstances, work, etc., in which he or she is placed; beginner; tyro.

old.Name: old
old.Description: far advanced in the years of one's or its life.

sick.Name: sick
sick.Description: afflicted with ill health or disease; ailing.

small.Name: small
small.Description: of limited size; of comparatively restricted dimensions; not big; little.

starving.Name: starving
starving.Description: to be in the process of perishing or suffering severely from hunger.

stiff.Name: stiff
stiff.Description: rigid or firm; difficult or impossible to bend or flex:
